WEBVTT

00:20.324 --> 00:22.805
D'Alessandro.
They made you captain?

00:22.892 --> 00:24.415
Hello, Johnson.

00:24.502 --> 00:27.462
I see you're back in cuffs,
where you belong.

00:27.549 --> 00:28.985
How's that house you bought
in the Jersey Shore

00:29.072 --> 00:30.682
with all that pat
that I used to pay you?

00:30.769 --> 00:32.554
Old dogs, new tricks.

00:32.641 --> 00:34.164
$20,000 down.

00:35.557 --> 00:39.126
The Reverend has asked me
to oversee the HARYOU program.

00:39.213 --> 00:44.131
And as she will be assuming
a very public position,

00:44.218 --> 00:46.133
we'll all have to keep
on the straight and narrow,

00:46.220 --> 00:47.743
now, won't we?

00:47.830 --> 00:50.311
I would love for you
to come with me to Africa

00:50.398 --> 00:52.530
after my trip to Mecca.

00:52.617 --> 00:55.664
I killed a man.
It was self-defense.

00:55.751 --> 00:58.623
There was a hit out on me.
My stepmother.

00:58.710 --> 01:01.626
If he wants me to secure Harlem
and Bumpy Johnson,

01:01.713 --> 01:04.281
I'm gonna need his influence
over the other bosses.

01:04.368 --> 01:05.978
Mr. Gigante would be willing

01:06.066 --> 01:08.155
to give you his support
under one condition--

01:08.242 --> 01:10.157
that you protect his daughter.

01:10.244 --> 01:13.377
You find her, keep her safe,
Chin will do what you ask.

01:13.464 --> 01:15.205
Joe Colombo, a friend
of your father's.

01:15.292 --> 01:17.860
- What do you want from me?
- I wanna help you.

01:17.947 --> 01:19.340
By kidnapping me?

01:19.427 --> 01:21.864
I'm proposing
a short-term bridge loan.

01:21.951 --> 01:24.693
Investing in your venture
was a terrible mistake.

01:24.780 --> 01:27.261
Venture?
Call it what it is, Judge.

01:27.348 --> 01:29.306
It was a heroin deal.

01:29.393 --> 01:32.179
You can't run Harlem alone, Ellsworth.

01:32.266 --> 01:33.267
You need an alliance.

01:33.354 --> 01:36.183
Set a meet with Jose Battle.

01:36.270 --> 01:37.793
But he's got men.
He's got guns.

01:37.880 --> 01:40.274
He can help us change
the balance of power.

01:40.361 --> 01:41.753
You want to be partners
with me?

01:41.840 --> 01:43.799
There's gonna be a war
in Harlem.

01:43.886 --> 01:45.496
The only war I'm interested
in fighting

01:45.583 --> 01:48.325
is the one to take back
my country, Cuba.

01:48.412 --> 01:50.327
We're both fighting to take
back our homelands.

01:50.414 --> 01:51.459
Mine is Harlem.

01:51.546 --> 01:53.330
Together, we'll be so strong

01:53.417 --> 01:56.203
the Italians
won't even dare start a war.

02:05.908 --> 02:11.218
♪ Ooh ♪

02:11.305 --> 02:15.352
♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪

02:15.439 --> 02:20.531
<i>♪ Ella es fuego a morir♪</i>

02:20.618 --> 02:25.232
<i>♪ Una en un millón,
lo sabe y te lo hará sentir♪</i>

02:25.319 --> 02:30.411
<i>♪ Peligrosa y también sutil♪</i>

02:30.498 --> 02:32.500
<i>♪ Un descuido, y te enamora,
te hará sufrir♪</i>

02:32.587 --> 02:35.242
<i>El dinero llama al dinero.</i>

02:35.329 --> 02:38.288
Money brings more money.

02:38.375 --> 02:40.334
As my Geechee ancestors
used to say,

02:40.421 --> 02:42.901
"Fire don't crack a full pot."

02:42.988 --> 02:44.642
Here's to keeping our pot full.

02:44.729 --> 02:46.470
<i>Salud.</i>

02:50.039 --> 02:52.302
I'm going to speak
for all us in saying

02:52.389 --> 02:54.391
it's been well worth the risk.

02:54.478 --> 02:57.960
Yes, yes.
Exceeding expectations.

02:58.047 --> 03:01.311
I told you, gentlemen,
I wouldn't steer you wrong.

03:01.398 --> 03:03.835
These go down awfully easy.

03:03.922 --> 03:05.359
Cuba Libres.

03:05.446 --> 03:07.274
That's rum,
Coca-Cola, and lime--

03:07.361 --> 03:10.277
the drink of Cuba's independence
since 19--

03:10.364 --> 03:11.800
Enough.

03:11.887 --> 03:14.411
Let's get the business
out of the way.

03:19.938 --> 03:22.854
Jesus, Bumpy, how much
are we talking about here?

03:22.941 --> 03:24.682
Nine-fifty.

03:24.769 --> 03:26.423
Well, that's substantially
more than last week.

03:26.510 --> 03:29.687
Why is that man
holding a gun?

03:29.774 --> 03:32.299
I told you I don't want
to be around any guns.

03:32.386 --> 03:34.301
Let's just finish
what we started.

03:34.388 --> 03:37.521
Then you can go back upstairs
and enjoy the party, alright?

03:37.608 --> 03:38.957
Fine.

03:40.872 --> 03:44.441
But if I ever see one more gun,
you can count me out.

03:57.454 --> 03:59.326
Let me tell you something.

03:59.413 --> 04:00.979
That fucking judge
better watch

04:01.066 --> 04:02.459
the way he fucking
look at me, man.

04:02.546 --> 04:03.982
I take my blade, I cut him

04:04.069 --> 04:06.028
across his big, fat
motherfucking ass.

04:06.115 --> 04:08.552
See how he likes sitting on the
fucking bench after that shit.

04:08.639 --> 04:12.556
He's difficult but manageable.
I can handle him.

04:15.429 --> 04:18.388
You handle everything.
I like the way you work.

04:18.475 --> 04:21.565
Combining our numbers was a nice
economy of scale, wasn't it?

04:21.652 --> 04:25.743
I'm talking about us as men,

04:25.830 --> 04:28.746
as people defending
their land against invaders.

04:31.009 --> 04:32.402
I need a favor from you.

04:32.489 --> 04:34.361
Anything serious?

04:34.448 --> 04:36.363
I just need you
to kill somebody.

04:39.627 --> 04:44.762
That's my sister, Riza.
Her husband, Santo.

04:44.849 --> 04:48.810
Their beautiful girls,
Savina and Severa, my nieces.

04:48.897 --> 04:50.551
You can't tell
from this photo,

04:50.638 --> 04:55.512
but my sister is pregnant
with her third child.

04:55.599 --> 04:58.559
It's a beautiful family.

04:58.646 --> 05:00.561
Sometime after this photo
was taken--

05:00.648 --> 05:02.693
I don't know, maybe
three weeks or something--

05:02.780 --> 05:06.436
their home was raided
by Fidel's men.

05:06.523 --> 05:13.530
My sister and my nieces
were tied together with wire

05:13.617 --> 05:17.447
and taken out
to behind the house.

05:17.534 --> 05:21.843
My brother-in-law was tied
to a chair, his eyes held open

05:21.930 --> 05:28.545
as they executed his family,
my family by firing squad.

05:31.505 --> 05:32.767
I'm sorry, Jose.

05:40.514 --> 05:43.995
The man responsible
for this is that guy.

05:44.082 --> 05:46.998
Madera. Juan Madera.

05:47.085 --> 05:49.566
One of Castro's most
trusted lieutenants.

05:49.653 --> 05:53.614
This garbage lied to me
about which side he was on

05:53.701 --> 05:56.530
and gave Fidel's men
the location of my family.

05:57.748 --> 06:00.011
Snitch.

06:00.098 --> 06:03.450
This Madera is here,
in New York City.

06:03.537 --> 06:05.452
My men are looking for him
in Spanish Harlem,

06:05.539 --> 06:08.455
but I think he might be hiding
in your neighborhood.

06:09.543 --> 06:10.370
We'll find him.

06:11.632 --> 06:12.850
And kill him.

06:14.156 --> 06:17.638
Before he escapes
back to Cuba.

06:17.725 --> 06:22.947
Bumpy, when I am a partner,
your problems become mine,

06:23.034 --> 06:25.559
and I hope that mine
become yours.

06:30.172 --> 06:31.652
Consider it done.

