08:02.743 --> 08:04.875
<i>♪ Just in case ♪</i>

08:13.275 --> 08:14.581
Name?

08:14.668 --> 08:15.930
Malik El-Shabazz.

08:16.017 --> 08:17.714
I am also known
as Malcolm X.

08:19.281 --> 08:22.589
- Malcolm X from America?
- Yes, sir.

08:22.676 --> 08:25.983
Uh, you'll find a letter signed
by Dr. Mahmoud Shawarbi

08:26.070 --> 08:28.769
of the United Nations attesting
to the fact I am a Muslim.

08:31.859 --> 08:36.603
This is not
an official document.

08:36.690 --> 08:40.998
Uh, Dr. Shawarbi assured me it
would, uh, suffice as such.

08:41.085 --> 08:44.262
Only the Maghama Sharia
can determine your status

08:44.349 --> 08:48.963
as a convert to Islam, and you
may not enter Mecca without it.

08:49.050 --> 08:52.053
Sir, with all due respect,
you know who I am.

08:52.140 --> 08:57.711
I have traveled very far to be
here, made many sacrifices.

08:57.798 --> 09:00.627
The Saudi ambassador himself
is the one who told me

09:00.714 --> 09:03.020
to have my visa
signed by Dr. Shawarbi.

09:03.107 --> 09:06.023
Then the Saudi ambassador
should have also informed you

09:06.110 --> 09:09.810
any attempt to enter
the Hajj as a non-Muslim

09:09.897 --> 09:12.160
is considered a crime
under Saudi law.

09:12.247 --> 09:13.596
Detain him.

09:14.945 --> 09:15.903
Come on.

09:32.441 --> 09:34.878
"Executive Director
Mayme Johnson

09:34.965 --> 09:37.794
stole the spotlight
last Saturday

09:37.881 --> 09:40.667
at the organization's meeting
at Benjamin Franklin High School

09:40.754 --> 09:44.801
when in her remarks preceding
Adam Clayton Powell,"

09:44.888 --> 09:47.761
"she announced
a national voter hotline

09:47.848 --> 09:50.198
to help black voters find
the right polling stations.

09:50.285 --> 09:53.244
Johnson's brilliant idea
was cheered

09:53.331 --> 09:59.076
by over 600 Harlemites
crammed in the gymnasium."

09:59.163 --> 10:01.862
Well, what can I say?
I learned from the best.

10:01.949 --> 10:04.995
Mm, and that's the only thing
you can say.

10:05.082 --> 10:07.694
You know, a smart master knows

10:07.781 --> 10:10.827
that the better
his student shines,

10:10.914 --> 10:14.178
the better he shines.

10:14.265 --> 10:18.226
Well, good, because she's about
about to be a whole lot shinier.

10:18.313 --> 10:19.619
Tell him.

10:20.707 --> 10:23.884
I just got off the phone
with Hamilton Tiegs, chairman

10:23.971 --> 10:26.103
of the National Newspaper
Publishers Association,

10:26.190 --> 10:28.802
and they have agreed
starting Wednesday

10:28.889 --> 10:31.892
to run "Get Out the Vote" ads
free of charge.

10:31.979 --> 10:34.938
Really?
Well, that is outstanding.

10:35.025 --> 10:37.375
Just make sure they
don't stick it in the back

10:37.462 --> 10:40.901
next to Hope's Horoscopes
and "used couch for sale."

10:43.294 --> 10:44.687
Mm-hmm?

10:46.036 --> 10:48.343
Someone from the District
Attorney's office is here.

10:48.430 --> 10:51.825
Oh, Lord have mercy.
What the hell do they want?

10:51.912 --> 10:53.435
Let him in.

10:55.350 --> 10:58.353
Is it a Christmas card
come early?

10:59.267 --> 11:02.444
Mayme Johnson,
you have been deposed

11:02.531 --> 11:03.880
by the United States Attorney

11:03.967 --> 11:05.099
for the Southern District
of New York.

11:12.323 --> 11:13.324
What?

11:15.370 --> 11:18.895
- Morgenthau?
- Morgenthau's in Washington.

11:18.982 --> 11:21.463
This is from Assistant District
Attorney Jonathan Pike.

11:21.550 --> 11:24.945
Oh, a real hard-ass,
from what I hear.

11:25.946 --> 11:27.817
He wants to meet at my apartment
this afternoon.

11:27.904 --> 11:29.819
House call?

11:29.906 --> 11:33.780
Oh. That's not good.

11:35.999 --> 11:38.349
Show this picture
to all of your runners.

11:38.436 --> 11:42.005
His name is Juan Madera.
Put the word out on the street.

11:42.092 --> 11:43.920
I wanna find him.

11:44.007 --> 11:45.400
What this guy do?

11:45.487 --> 11:47.010
Something horrible in Cuba.

11:47.097 --> 11:49.926
Why we gotta do
Battle's dirty work for him?

11:50.013 --> 11:51.841
He helped us with Joe Colombo.

11:51.928 --> 11:53.321
And when the next duji shipment
comes in,

11:53.408 --> 11:55.236
we'll need him for men,
money, and guns,

11:55.323 --> 11:58.065
so if we gotta do some bullshit
favor, then we do it.

11:59.501 --> 12:02.025
Okay. Okay.

12:02.112 --> 12:04.158
So we'll check out
this Madera cat.

12:04.245 --> 12:06.813
I want you to find
this motherfucker

12:06.900 --> 12:08.423
and you kill him.

12:17.954 --> 12:21.131
Can I please get
a glass of water?

13:02.564 --> 13:04.479
Do you speak English?

13:11.051 --> 13:12.269
Floor.

13:14.010 --> 13:14.924
Floor.

13:16.970 --> 13:18.275
Ceiling.

13:19.973 --> 13:23.280
- Ceiling.
- Mm-hmm.

13:23.367 --> 13:25.587
Muhammad Ali. Clay?

13:25.674 --> 13:28.503
Ali?

13:28.590 --> 13:29.939
Muhammad Ali?

13:30.026 --> 13:32.202
Muhammad Ali!

13:32.289 --> 13:34.161
No, no, not me. Not me.

13:34.248 --> 13:37.033
But I know him.
It looks like you do too.

13:37.120 --> 13:39.079
- Muhammad Ali?
- No.

13:39.166 --> 13:43.039
Yeah. Name Muhammad Ali.
Muhammad Ali.

13:43.648 --> 13:45.476
But why would the
assistant district attorney

13:45.563 --> 13:47.261
wanna meet with me?

13:47.348 --> 13:48.915
I mean, other than something
having to do with you.

13:49.002 --> 13:50.917
The feds got no case
against me right now.

13:51.004 --> 13:53.397
Oh, it just feels so ominous.

13:53.484 --> 13:56.531
That's what they want it to feel
like. Don't worry about it.

13:58.011 --> 13:59.926
I just don't want this
to jeopardize

14:00.013 --> 14:01.710
everything I'm building
right now.

14:01.797 --> 14:03.364
This is what happens
when your profile gets raised.

14:03.451 --> 14:06.062
You know that.

14:06.149 --> 14:08.064
I guess so.

14:08.151 --> 14:10.632
In fact, it's probably Powell
they wanna talk to you about.

14:10.719 --> 14:13.069
Those Dixiecrats
are looking for dirt

14:13.156 --> 14:15.376
to derail
his voting rights bill.

14:15.463 --> 14:21.512
Look, go talk to this guy Pike.
No big deal.

14:21.599 --> 14:26.343
You've done nothing wrong
and you got nothing to hide.

14:33.263 --> 14:35.135
Thank you.

15:13.303 --> 15:19.092
I--I know it's not much,
but it'll do, you know, for now.

15:19.179 --> 15:20.571
How long are you
keeping me here for?

15:20.658 --> 15:23.139
Until I'm certain
that you're safe.

15:23.226 --> 15:24.619
I can keep myself safe.

15:27.100 --> 15:30.581
Someone tried to
have you killed, Stella.

15:30.668 --> 15:32.540
They may try it again.

15:32.627 --> 15:36.674
And I made a promise to your
pops that I'd look after you.

15:36.761 --> 15:40.591
How do you know he wasn't
the one who tried to whack me?

15:40.678 --> 15:42.158
Come on, what are
you talking about?

15:42.245 --> 15:45.553
He's the one asking me
to protect you.

15:45.640 --> 15:47.163
Listen.

15:47.250 --> 15:51.080
I'll get you some
new furniture, wallpaper,

15:51.167 --> 15:53.300
spruce the place up, and...

15:53.387 --> 15:56.129
And then you-- you
expect me to just, what,

15:56.216 --> 15:59.045
sit here all day long?

16:00.524 --> 16:03.049
What would you like to do?

16:03.136 --> 16:07.053
If I'm staying here,
I'm going back to school.

16:07.140 --> 16:09.055
And I'm gonna get a job.

16:09.142 --> 16:13.755
School can wait, but I think
I might have a job for you.

16:14.712 --> 16:16.279
What's that?

16:16.366 --> 16:19.065
Working for me.

16:19.152 --> 16:21.067
Come on.

16:37.344 --> 16:39.781
<i>As-salamu alaykum,</i> Malcolm.

16:39.868 --> 16:41.217
It is a great honor
to meet you.

16:41.304 --> 16:44.481
<i>Wa-alaykum-Salaam.</i>
And you are?

16:44.568 --> 16:46.266
Dr. Omar Azzam.

16:46.353 --> 16:48.181
Welcome to Mecca.

16:48.268 --> 16:51.227
A prison cell is not
my idea of a welcome.

16:51.314 --> 16:54.317
No, of course not.
I am so sorry.

16:54.404 --> 16:56.798
I am here to help you with that.

16:56.885 --> 16:59.366
Your arrival here in Mecca
has caused quite a stir

16:59.453 --> 17:01.498
in the international press.

17:01.585 --> 17:03.674
The Royal Family itself asked me

17:03.761 --> 17:05.807
to help petition the Maghama
Sharia on your behalf.

17:05.894 --> 17:08.244
Well, that's just fine.
Thank you.

17:08.331 --> 17:13.119
See? Allah answers our prayers,
especially in Mecca.

17:13.206 --> 17:16.122
Thank you, Dr. Azzam.

17:16.209 --> 17:19.560
Perhaps you'd be so kind
to give me a lift to my hotel.

17:19.647 --> 17:21.127
I'm sorry.
You cannot go there.

17:21.214 --> 17:22.954
Why not?

17:23.042 --> 17:24.304
The Sharia court will
not be able to hear your case

17:24.391 --> 17:26.654
for several days yet.

17:26.741 --> 17:29.309
I see.

17:29.396 --> 17:31.572
My friend, forgive me
for not being clear.

17:31.659 --> 17:33.139
You do not have to stay here.

17:33.226 --> 17:36.403
You can leave,
but with a chaperone.

17:36.490 --> 17:39.232
And who might that be?

17:39.319 --> 17:43.149
I invite you to come stay
with my family in my home.

17:43.236 --> 17:46.413
- In your home?
- Yes.

17:46.500 --> 17:50.243
I've never been invited
to a white man's home before.

17:50.330 --> 17:52.245
Praise Allah. Now you have.

17:52.332 --> 17:55.248
Of course,
if you'd rather stay here...

18:01.297 --> 18:02.951
<i>Salaam alaykum.</i>

18:03.038 --> 18:04.779
- Goodbye, Muhammad Ali.
- Goodbye, Muhammad Ali.

18:09.262 --> 18:12.091
Dr. Azzam, please lead the way.

18:16.965 --> 18:20.229
Mr. Pike,
why are we here?

18:20.316 --> 18:22.405
You're the new director
of HARYOU, are you not?

18:22.492 --> 18:24.451
Yes.

18:24.538 --> 18:26.714
HARYOU has accepted
